5. 'Stale Statistics' kya hota hai ?

=> 👉 Jab table ka data kaafi change ho jata hai (insert, update, delete se), tab purane statistics outdated / stale ho jaate hain.

	👉 Oracle generally stats ko stale mark karta hai jab table ke around 10% ya usse zyada rows change ho jati hain.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

6. What is the 'Stale statistics status' ?

=> 📌 Whenever any table needs to 'stale gather' oracle enable the 'stale stats on' feature of that table. And, then we as a DBA do stats gathered on these table where the stale stats on.

	📌How to do that - 

✅ GATHER_TABLE_STATS - for tables
✅ GATHER_SCHEMA_STATS - for schema
✅ GATHER_DATABASE_STATS - for DB
✅ GATHER_INDEX_STATS - for index

⚡ Check if any table has stale stats or not -

📌 View - desc dba_tab_statistics;
📌 select owner, index_name, stale_stats from dba_ind_statistics where stale_stats='YES' and owner='HR';

⚡ If stale stats 'YES' found then how to gather states - 
📌 command - exec DBMS_STATS.GATHER_TABLE_STATS (ownname => 'HR', tabname => 'EMP');

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

