6. What is DB time and Elapsed time ?

=>	 📌DB Time :: Total time spent inside the database. 
				Includes: CPU time + Wait time (like waiting for I/O, locks, etc.) 
				Only counts the time when the session is actively working or waiting in the database.

				DB Time = SUM (All SQL CPU time) + SUM (ALL SQL wait time)

 				🔍 Think of it like ::
				"How much time your database was busy working or waiting on something for a user's request."

	📌Elapsed Time :: Total time taken from start to finish for a task or operation.

					Includes everything - idle time, DB time, network delay, application-side wait, etc.
					It's the total clock time.

					🔍 Think of it like ::
					"How much time it actually took for the task to complete — including database and non-database parts."

	🔍 Use Case Example ::
				Let’s say a user runs a report that takes 10 seconds to finish.

				DB Time might be 6 seconds (actual work in DB like fetching, joining, waiting on I/O).

				Elapsed Time is 10 seconds (includes 4 seconds of waiting outside the DB — maybe in the app or network).

