11. What is Defragmentation ?

=>	📌 Cleaning up the database storage so that, space is used more efficiently and data is stored continuously.

	🎯 Why Do Fragmentation Happen?

	📌 When rows are inserted, updated, or deleted frequently
	📌 Oracle may leave gaps inside data blocks
	📌 Over time, tables and indexes get fragmented
	📌 This leads to wasted space and slower performance

	⚡ Purpose of Defragmentation

	📌 Free up unused space	      
	📌 Improve query performance
	📌 Data is stored more compactly, so less I/O
	📌 Makes tablespaces smaller or reusable

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

